?><p>Which of us doesn’t dream of a white Hollywood smile? Especially if it is possible just in one hour! In our office we offer you in office bleaching system – single-visit in office whitening.</p>

<p>Whiter teeth, in about one hour. It's that simple. Years of yellowing as well as staining from virtually everything you eat, drink, and inhale are almost magically erased in the time it takes to get a haircut, a manicure or lunch. In fact, In Office Whitening has a new and improved professional teeth whitening treatment that gets teeth an average of 9+ shades! And it's still just one hour.</p>

<p>In-Office Whitening offers clients the safety and science of a dentist's office with all the comforts of a spa. First you'll have a complimentary consultation to answer all your questions. Your dentist will then examine your teeth and gums to ensure that they're healthy for whitening at that time. Then, while you relax, watch TV or even nap, our proprietary gel and blue light treatment work to whiten teeth to their optimal brightness.</p>

<p>We use the latest bleaching product The Brite Smile In Office-Whitening System. It is the safest and most effective procedure which provides you a snow-white smile! You can learn more about Brite Smile at www.britesmile.com.</p>

<p>What does the whole procedure look like?</p>
<ol>
<li>Gums and mouth are protected with isolation materials and a "Before" picture is taken.</li>
<li>The whitening gel is professionally applied and activated by the light source.</li>
<li>After three 20-minute applications over a one-hour period, your whitening is completed and your "After" picture is taken.</li>
<li>You rinse. You smile. Wow!</li>
</ol>
<p>This is simply a great way to a whiter, healthier looking smile.</p>

<p>You can feel confident in your decision to have dental professionals whiten your teeth. Clinical testing has proven that the procedure is safe and sound. Safety studies conducted at the University of Medicine and Dentistry of New Jersey found conclusively that In-Office Whitening resulted in no structural change in teeth; no adverse impacts on fillings and no softening of tooth enamel.</p>

<p>What it all means for you is that our whitening results confirm an average of 9+ shades whiter and even higher for individuals with darker teeth. Years of coffee, cigarettes, red wine and other stains seem to magically disappear. And success is so certain, your whitening is guaranteed!</p>

<h2>Home bleaching</h2>
<p>At-home procedure, sometimes called nightguard vital bleaching, consist of placing a bleaching solution, usually a peroxide mixture, in a tray (nightguard) that has been custom fitted for your mouth by an oral health care professional. The bleaching solutions may vary in potency and may be worn for an hour, or throughout the night. Besides the concentration of the active agent home bleacing systems is lower than of that in professional system therefore it takes a longet time to complete this whitening. Your oral health care professional can advise you on the appropriate type of application and the length of time needed to whiten your teeth, based on the severity of tooth discoloration and your specific needs.</p><?require($_SERVER["DOCUMENT_ROOT"].SITE_TEMPLATE_PATH."/fixedwidth-footer.php"); require($_SERVER["DOCUMENT_ROOT"]."/bitrix/footer.php");?>